library(igraph)
g <- igraph::barabasi.game(n=100)
layout <- layout.auto(g)
# Plotting with configuration
plot(g, 
     edge.arrow.size=.5, 
     vertex.color="white", 
     vertex.size=4,
     vertex.frame.color="red", 
     vertex.label.color="black", 
     vertex.label.cex=0.5, 
     vertex.label.dist=1.2, 
     edge.curved=0,
     layout=layout)

We cannot make clusters because everything are the connected. However, we can remove the central node to breaking network into pieces.

Letâs find the central node by the degree centrality

V(g)[degree(g) == max(degree(g))]
## + 1/100 vertex, from 6eccc57:
## [1] 1

Nr 1 is the node that has max connection.

g = delete_vertices(g,"1")
layout <- layout.auto(g)
# Plotting with configuration
plot(g, 
     edge.arrow.size=.5, 
     vertex.color="white", 
     vertex.size=4,
     vertex.frame.color="red", 
     vertex.label.color="black", 
     vertex.label.cex=0.5, 
     vertex.label.dist=1.2, 
     edge.curved=0,
     layout=layout)

## Dethroning

Isolated = which(degree(g)==0) 
g_post_king = delete.vertices(g, Isolated)
layout <- layout.auto(g_post_king)
# Plotting with configuration
plot(g_post_king, 
     edge.arrow.size=.5, 
     vertex.color="white", 
     vertex.size=4,
     vertex.frame.color="red", 
     vertex.label.color="black", 
     vertex.label.cex=0.5, 
     vertex.label.dist=1.2, 
     edge.curved=0,
     layout=layout)
